ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You have to do a senior project anyway, and it's kind of fun to meet the other Applied Math/Stats majors every week and chat about your progress / random stuff. It's only 2 hours a week, and it ended up being pretty enjoyable throughout, so I don't see why you would choose to do an independent project unless this class conflicts with your schedule.

NO. DO THE PROJECT NOT THE SEMINAR. As long as you schedule a biweekly meeting with your adviser, it's not really necessary to sit through the seminar. It's not useful, and just adds more work in addition to the project.
